covidLtcNotes.notes:
Idaho reports long-term care data for Nursing Homes, Assisted Living Facilities, and Intermediate Care Facilities. Idaho reports both cumulative and outbreak cases and deaths for Long-Term Care Facilities. Idaho does not provide data for when the cumulative totals were first recorded. Idaho reports lab-confirmed and probable COVID cases combined. Idaho defines a probable case as a person who had symptoms of COVID-19 and was exposed to someone with a lab-confirmed case of COVID-19, but has no positive laboratory test confirming COVID-19 infection. Resident and staff cases and deaths are combined.

Idaho defines an outbreak as at least one lab-confirmed or probable COVID-positive case associated with a facility. An outbreak is considered resolved when more than 28 days pass without any additional cases associated with the facility.

June 5, 2020: Idaho began releasing weekly reports about long-term care information. CTP began using this data set to report Long-Term Care Facilities.
